<h2 id="procedure">Test Procedure (IS 6792)</h2>

<Callout type="warning" title="HV safety — do not touch test cell during test">
  <p>The BDV test applies up to 80–100 kV AC. Never open or touch the test cell enclosure during the test. All CIE oil test sets have an interlocked door that cuts power if opened.</p>
</Callout>

<div class="my-6 space-y-0">
  {[
    { n:1, t:'Collect a representative oil sample', b:'Draw oil from the transformer drain valve using clean, dry, glass or polypropylene sample bottles. Fill from below the surface to avoid atmospheric moisture. Label with transformer ID, date, and temperature.' },
    { n:2, t:'Allow sample to reach ambient temperature', b:'Bring the sample to 20–30 °C. Test oil that is too hot or too cold gives unrepresentative results.' },
    { n:3, t:'Clean and dry the test cell', b:'Rinse the test cell with a small amount of the oil sample itself. Wipe electrodes with clean, lint-free cloth. Moisture in the cell gives false low readings.' },
    { n:4, t:'Fill the test cell and wait', b:'Pour oil into the cell and wait 10 minutes for air bubbles to escape. Bubbles conduct and give false low BDV.' },
    { n:5, t:'Apply voltage at 2 kV/second', b:'IS 6792 specifies raising voltage at 2 kV/s continuously until breakdown occurs. The instrument records the arc-over voltage automatically.' },
    { n:6, t:'Repeat 6 times, record average', b:'IS 6792 requires 6 breakdown tests on the same sample with 2-minute intervals between each (to allow the oil to degas). The average of all 6 is the BDV result.' },
  ].map((s, i, arr) => (
    <div class="flex gap-4 relative">
      {i < arr.length - 1 && <div class="absolute left-5 top-10 bottom-0 w-0.5 bg-[#E0252E]/20"></div>}
      <div class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-[#E0252E] text-white font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center z-10 shadow">{s.n}</div>
      <div class="pb-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-[#0D1B2A]">{s.t}</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-0.5">{s.b}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  ))}
</div>

<h2 id="interpreting">Interpreting BDV Results (IS 335 / IS 1866)</h2>

<div class="my-8 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden">
  <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
    <thead>
      <tr class="bg-[#0D1B2A]">
        <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-[#94a3b8] font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest">BDV Result (Average)</th>
        <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-white font-semibold">Condition</th>
        <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-white font-semibold">Action</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {[
        ['> 70 kV', 'Excellent — new oil condition', 'No action required'],
        ['50–70 kV', 'Good — acceptable for service', 'Continue normal monitoring schedule'],
        ['30–50 kV', 'Marginal — investigate', 'Filter / dry the oil. Increase monitoring frequency.'],
        ['< 30 kV', 'Poor — immediate action required', 'Do not energise. Filter and retest, or replace oil.'],
        ['< 10 kV', 'Critical / severely contaminated', 'Replace oil immediately. Inspect for internal fault.'],
      ].map(([bdv, cond, action], i) => (
        <tr class={i % 2 === 0 ? 'bg-white' : 'bg-gray-50'}>
          <td class={`px-5 py-3 font-mono font-bold border-b border-gray-100 text-xs ${i >= 3 ? 'text-[#E0252E]' : i === 2 ? 'text-amber-600' : 'text-emerald-600'}`}>{bdv}</td>
          <td class="px-5 py-3 text-[#0D1B2A] font-medium border-b border-gray-100 text-xs">{cond}</td>
          <td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-600 border-b border-gray-100 text-xs">{action}</td>
        </tr>
      ))}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<Callout type="info" title="BDV is one of several oil tests">
  <p>BDV alone does not give a complete picture of oil condition. A full oil analysis (DGA — Dissolved Gas Analysis, moisture content, acidity, interfacial tension) is needed for major transformer maintenance decisions. BDV is the routine screening test; DGA is the diagnostic test.</p>
</Callout>

